getBondOrder

int getBondOrder()
Gets the bond order for this bond. Please remember that you can check the aromaticity also via the aromaticity flag, which is the better way. The Bond.JOE_AROMATIC_BOND_ORDER which can be assigned to the bond order is only needed for some awkward import/export methods. Please remember that the aromaticity typer JOEAromaticTyper.assignAromaticFlags(Molecule) assign ONLY aromaticity flags and NOT the internal aromatic bond order Bond.JOE_AROMATIC_BOND_ORDER.

Returns:
The bond order

hashCode

int hashCode()
Calculates the hashcode for a bond. Includes order, flags and equality of begin and end atom. Excludes the bond index number. The begin and end atom are included using their hashcode methods.

setBondOrder

void setBondOrder(int order)
Sets the bond order for this bond. This causes no change in the aromaticity flag for this bond. Please remember that the aromaticity typer JOEAromaticTyper.assignAromaticFlags(Molecule) assign ONLY aromaticity flags and NOT the internal aromatic bond order Bond.JOE_AROMATIC_BOND_ORDER.

Parameters:
order - the new bond order
